    public class MaterialFloatBox
extends MaterialNumberBox<Float>
    Material Float Box is an input field that accepts any Float based string from user.

    UiBinder Usage:

      <m:MaterialFloatBox ui:field="txtFloatBox" label="Float value"/>

 // Setting value in Java
 txtFloatBox.setValue(1000.25f);

    The parsing and formatting of the number are done natively by the browser, using the i18n settings from the user.

    Author:
    paulux84
    See Also:
    Material FloatBox, Material Design Specification
